---
/* ✅ CHANGE THIS import to match src/pages/guides/mental-health/index.astro */
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "Aging & Longevity";
const description =
  "Guides and analysis on aging biology, lifespan heritability, and the difference between intrinsic and extrinsic mortality.";
const canonical = "https://patientguide.io/guides/aging-longevity";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <!-- JSON-LD: Breadcrumbs -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://patientguide.io/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Guides", "item": "https://patientguide.io/guides" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Aging & Longevity", "item": canonical }
      ]
    })}
  </script>

  <!-- JSON-LD: ItemList -->
  <script type=”application/ld+json” is:inline>
    {JSON.stringify({
      “@context”: “https://schema.org”,
      “@type”: “ItemList”,
      “name”: “Aging & Longevity – featured reading”,
      “itemListElement”: [
        {
          “@type”: “ListItem”,
          “position”: 1,
          “name”: “Aging and Longevity Basics”,
          “url”: “https://patientguide.io/guides/aging-and-longevity-basics”
        },
        {
          “@type”: “ListItem”,
          “position”: 2,
          “name”: “Healthspan vs Lifespan”,
          “url”: “https://patientguide.io/guides/healthspan-vs-lifespan”
        },
        {
          “@type”: “ListItem”,
          “position”: 3,
          “name”: “The Hallmarks of Aging Explained”,
          “url”: “https://patientguide.io/guides/hallmarks-of-aging”
        },
        {
          “@type”: “ListItem”,
          “position”: 4,
          “name”: “Longevity Lifestyle Basics”,
          “url”: “https://patientguide.io/guides/longevity-lifestyle-basics”
        },
        {
          “@type”: “ListItem”,
          “position”: 5,
          “name”: “Longevity Interventions: What Has Evidence?”,
          “url”: “https://patientguide.io/guides/longevity-interventions-evidence”
        }
      ]
    })}
  </script>

  <main class=”page”>
    <header class=”hub-hero”>
      <h1>{title}</h1>
      <p>{description}</p>
      <p>Aging research is shifting from treating diseases individually to understanding the shared biological processes that increase vulnerability over time. This hub organizes those concepts — from mortality theory to molecular mechanisms to what you can actually do about it.</p>
    </header>

    <section class=”hub-section”>
      <h2>🧭 Start Here — Foundations</h2>
      <p>If you're new to longevity science, begin with these core concepts.</p>
      <ol class=”reading-order”>
        <li>
          <a href=”/guides/aging-and-longevity-basics”>Aging and Longevity Basics</a>
          <p>What aging is, what longevity means, and what actually changes in the body over time.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href=”/guides/healthspan-vs-lifespan”>Healthspan vs Lifespan</a>
          <p>Why living longer and living well aren't the same thing.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href=”/guides/biological-age-vs-chronological-age”>Biological Age vs Chronological Age</a>
          <p>How your body's age can diverge from the calendar — and why it matters.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href=”/guides/what-determines-human-lifespan”>What Determines Human Lifespan?</a>
          <p>Genetics, environment, and lifestyle — how much each factor actually contributes.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href=”/guides/intrinsic-vs-extrinsic-mortality”>Intrinsic vs Extrinsic Mortality</a>
          <p>The key distinction that clarifies most debates about aging, genetics, and longevity.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class=”hub-section”>
      <h2>🧬 Mechanisms</h2>
      <p>How aging actually happens at the biological level.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href=”/guides/hallmarks-of-aging”>The Hallmarks of Aging Explained</a>
          <p>The core biological processes that drive aging — and how they shape healthspan, lifespan, and disease risk.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href=”/guides/epigenetics-and-aging”>Epigenetics and Aging</a>
          <p>How gene expression changes with age — and what epigenetic clocks can and can't tell us.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class=”hub-section”>
      <h2>🏃 Lifestyle & Interventions</h2>
      <p>What the evidence actually supports for extending healthspan.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href=”/guides/longevity-lifestyle-basics”>Longevity Lifestyle Basics</a>
          <p>Sleep, exercise, diet, and stress — the foundations with the strongest evidence base.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href=”/guides/longevity-interventions-evidence”>Longevity Interventions: What Has Evidence?</a>
          <p>A clear-eyed review of supplements, drugs, and protocols — what's supported and what's hype.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class=”hub-section”>
      <h2>💪 Muscle, Metabolism & Aging</h2>
      <p>Two of the most modifiable drivers of how well you age.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href=”/guides/sarcopenia-aging”>Sarcopenia: Muscle Loss with Age</a>
          <p>Why muscle mass declines, why it matters, and the evidence on resistance training and protein.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href=”/guides/glp-1-drugs-and-aging”>GLP-1 Drugs and Aging</a>
          <p>What weight-loss medicines mean for older adults — benefits, muscle risk, and practical guidance.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class=”hub-section”>
      <h2>🧴 Skin & Appearance Aging</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href=”/guides/skin-aging”>Skin Aging: Causes, Prevention, and Treatment</a>
          <p>What drives skin aging intrinsically and extrinsically — and what topical treatments have real evidence.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class=”hub-section”>
      <h2>📰 Analysis & Debate</h2>
      <p>Where longevity science challenges conventional thinking.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href=”/posts/longevity-genetics-rehabilitated”>Longevity Genetics Just Got Rehabilitated</a>
          <p>New evidence suggesting intrinsic human lifespan may be ~50–55% heritable once confounding deaths are removed.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href=”/posts/lifestyle-over-genes-dogma”>How “Lifestyle Over Genes” Became Medical Dogma</a>
          <p>Why aging genetics were sidelined — and why that story is now collapsing.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
